Package net.viktorc.pp4j.impl

Class JavaProcessPoolExecutor

  • Object
    • ProcessPoolExecutor
      • JavaProcessPoolExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Executor, ExecutorService, JavaProcessExecutorService, ProcessExecutor, ProcessExecutorService
    public class JavaProcessPoolExecutor
extends ProcessPoolExecutor
implements JavaProcessExecutorService
    A sub-class of ProcessPoolExecutor that implements the JavaProcessExecutorService interface. It manages Java processes to implement a multiprocessing mechanism with the same API as that of the standard Java thread pools. It communicates with the processes via their standard streams exchanging serialized and encoded Java objects. It sends tasks to the processes for execution and it receives the results or exceptions thrown in return.
    Author:
    Viktor Csomor

    • Constructor Detail

      • JavaProcessPoolExecutor

        public JavaProcessPoolExecutor​(JavaProcessManagerFactory<T> processManagerFactory,
                               int minPoolSize,
                               int maxPoolSize,
                               int reserveSize,
                               long threadKeepAliveTime)
                        throws InterruptedException
        Constructs a Java process pool executor using the specified parameters.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the startup task.
        Parameters:
        processManagerFactory - The java process manager factory.
        minPoolSize - The minimum size of the process pool.
        maxPoolSize - The maximum size of the process pool.
        reserveSize - The number of available processes to keep in the pool.
        threadKeepAliveTime - The number of milliseconds of idleness after which threads are terminated if the sizes of the thread pools exceed their core sizes.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - If the thread is interrupted while it is waiting for the core threads to start up.
        IllegalArgumentException - If options is null, the minimum pool size is less than 0, or the maximum pool size is less than the minimum pool size or 1, or the reserve size is less than 0 or greater than the maximum pool size.
